        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 6:10PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 609 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Turkey, moving northeast at 20 mph.  This
activity extended into western Hall county and eastern Briscoe
county.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Turkey, Caprock Canyon State Park, Quitaque, Valley Schools, and
Flomot.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
